      "description": "The Corgi Emerging Markets Equities 15% Structured Buffer ETF - June Series (EMJN) is an exchange-traded fund that mostly invests in downside hedge alternatives. The fund seeks to provide investors with returns that generally match the price return (excluding dividends) of the iShares Russell 2000 ETF, up to the upside cap of 19.59% (prior to taking into account management fees and other fees) while providing a buffer against the first 15% (prior to taking into account management fees and other fees) of iS. EMJN was launched on Jun 1, 2026 and is issued by Corgi.",
